# Project architecture

See README.md for the full directory map.

## Layer responsibilities

- `api/{resource}/` — HTTP only: fetch functions + request/response types. No React.
- `data/` — TanStack Query hooks and query keys. Imports from `@api/`, not from features.
- `components/` — Shared UI primitives. No imports from `@app/` or `@features/`.
- `features/{Feature}/` — Everything for one feature: page, sub-components, hooks, styles.
- `app/` — Wires it all together: routes, providers, navigation.
- `lib/` — Thin wrappers re-exporting third-party packages. All app code imports from here.
- `models/` — Domain types only. All entities extend `BaseEntity` from `models/base.ts`.

## Import direction

```
app → features → components / data / api → lib / models / theme
```

No layer imports from a layer above it. `components/` never imports from `features/` or `app/`.

## Feature isolation

To remove a feature: delete its folder, remove it from `app/routes` and `app/navigation`. Nothing else should reference it.

## API models

```
api/models.ts           → ApiItemResponse<T>, ApiListResponse<T>, ApiError
api/{resource}/
  apiModels.ts          → ResourceResponse, UpdateResourcePayload (extends api/models)
  index.ts              → fetch functions using apiModels types
```

`UpdatePayload` omits `id` — it is never sent in the request body.
